National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice recently met with senior Chinese officials in Beijing to prepare for Chinese President Xi Jinping's upcoming visit to the United States. The discussions covered a wide range of bilateral, regional, and global issues, including Iran, North Korea, climate change, and global public health. Rice emphasized the importance of expanding cooperation and addressing differences constructively, particularly on issues such as cyber, Chinese currency, maritime concerns, and human rights. Rice also engaged in productive discussions with Chinese officials on economic, military, trade, and development matters. In a meeting with President Xi, Rice reaffirmed the commitment to further practical cooperation in areas of mutual interest and to address disagreements openly and effectively.